HEADWORD: Roughhewn
<hw>Rough"hewn`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Hewn
coarsely without smoothing; unfinished; not polished.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of coarse manners; rude; uncultivated;
rough-grained.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>roughhewn</xex> seaman.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roughing-in</ent>⟦br⟧
